Ask HN: Why not require apps using up a lot of CPU to provide a reason to user?
text:
For example, if a podcasts app is using up a lot of CPU and it normally doesn't do so, should you force quit it?

If apps are required to provide a reason for using high level of CPU for an extended period of time, then this would help the user decide whether to force quit the app.
